<h3>Name</h3>
<blockquote><b>pljava</b> - a utility for running Java programs which
use the Pipeline Java API.<br>
</blockquote>
<h3>Synopsis</h3>
<blockquote><b>pljava</b> [<a href="#Global_Options"><i>options</i></a>]
  <span style="font-weight: bold;">--jar</span>=<span
 style="font-style: italic;">program.jar</span><span
 style="font-style: italic;"></span><span style="font-weight: bold;"></span>
[<span style="font-weight: bold;">--main</span>=<span
 style="font-style: italic;">mainclass</span>]&nbsp; [<span
 style="font-weight: bold;">--</span> <span style="font-style: italic;">args</span>
...] <br>
  <b>pljava</b> [<a href="pljava.src.html.in#Global_Options"><i>options</i></a>]&nbsp;<span
 style="font-weight: bold;"></span><span style="font-weight: bold;">--classpath</span>=<span
 style="font-style: italic;">classdir </span>[<span
 style="font-weight: bold;">--classpath</span>=...<span
 style="font-style: italic;"></span>] <span style="font-weight: bold;">--main</span>=<span
 style="font-style: italic;">mainclass&nbsp; </span><span
 style="font-style: italic;"></span><span style="font-weight: bold;"></span>
[<span style="font-weight: bold;">--</span> <span
 style="font-style: italic;">args</span> ...]<br>
  <b>pljava</b> [<a href="pljava.src.html.in#Global_Options"><i>options</i></a>]
  <span style="font-weight: bold;">--source</span>=<span
 style="font-style: italic;">program.java&nbsp; </span><span
 style="font-style: italic;"></span><span style="font-weight: bold;"></span>
[<span style="font-weight: bold;">--</span> <span
 style="font-style: italic;">args</span> ...] <br>
  <br>
  <b>pljava</b> <a href="#--help" style="font-weight: bold;">--help</a><br>
  <b>pljava</b> <a href="#--html-help" style="font-weight: bold;">--html-help</a><br>
  <b>pljava</b> <a href="#--version_" style="font-weight: bold;">--version</a><br>
  <b>pljava</b> <a href="#--release-date" style="font-weight: bold;">--release-date</a><br>
  <b>pljava</b> <a href="#--copyright" style="font-weight: bold;">--copyright</a><br>
  <span style="font-weight: bold;">pljava <a href="#--license">--license</a></span><br>
</blockquote>
<h3><a name="Description"></a>Description</h3>
<blockquote>This tool uses the Java Runtime Enviroment (JRE) to execute
a Java based program which makes use of the Pipeline API.&nbsp; This
tool is not strictly necessary, but makes it easier to run Pipeline
related programs by managing the fairly complex set of command-line
options which must be provided to the <span style="font-weight: bold;">java</span>(1)
program in order to take advantage of the Pipeline API.<br>
</blockquote>
<div style="margin-left: 40px;">There are three ways that the Java
program can be specified:&nbsp; <br>
</div>
<div style="margin-left: 40px;">
<ol>
</ol>
<span style="font-weight: bold;">--jar</span>=<span
 style="font-style: italic;">program.jar</span><span
 style="font-style: italic;"></span><span style="font-weight: bold;"></span>
[<span style="font-weight: bold;">--main</span>=<span
 style="font-style: italic;">mainclass</span>]<br>
<div style="margin-left: 40px;"><br>
The class files that make up the program have been packaged into an
Java Archive (<span style="font-style: italic;">program.jar</span>)
using <span style="font-weight: bold;">jar</span>(1).&nbsp; If the
Manifest of the supplied JAR file includes a "Main-Class" entry, then
it's "main" method will be executed as the entry point for the
program.&nbsp; Alternatively, the entry point class can be specified on
the command-line using the <span style="font-weight: bold;">--main</span>
option instead.&nbsp;&nbsp; Either way, the entry point class (<span
 style="font-style: italic;">mainclass</span>) should be specified as
using a fully resolved class name which includes any package
prefixes.&nbsp; If a <span style="font-weight: bold;">--main</span>
option is given, it will override and "Main-Class" specified in the
Manifest of the JAR file.&nbsp; <br>
<br>
</div>
<span style="font-weight: bold;">--classpath</span>=<span
 style="font-style: italic;">classdir </span>[<span
 style="font-weight: bold;">--classpath</span>=<span
 style="font-style: italic;"></span>...<span style="font-style: italic;"></span>]&nbsp;
<span style="font-weight: bold;">--main</span>=<span
 style="font-style: italic;">mainclass<br>
<br>
</span>
<div style="margin-left: 40px;">The class files are not packaged, but
instead live under one or more directories (<span
 style="font-style: italic;">classdir</span>) who's structure mirrors
that of the Java package heirarchy.&nbsp; Each of these package root
directories is specified with a separate <span
 style="font-weight: bold;">--classpath</span> option.&nbsp; With this
approach the entry point class (<span style="font-style: italic;">mainclass</span>)
must be provided using the <span style="font-weight: bold;">--main</span>
option.<br>
</div>
<span style="font-weight: bold;"><br>
--source</span>=<span style="font-style: italic;">program.java</span><br>
<div style="margin-left: 40px;"><br>
Normally, a developer would use <span style="font-weight: bold;">javac</span>(1)
is to compile Java source code files into Java bytecode and then used
either the <span style="font-weight: bold;">--jar</span> or <span
 style="font-weight: bold;">--classpath</span> methods to run the
resulting bytecode.&nbsp; Although this is the most efficient way and
recommended way of creating Java programs, it can be inconvenient when
writing very simple single class programs.&nbsp; When only one class is
required, it can be useful to be able to compile and then run it all in
one step.&nbsp; Using this <span style="font-weight: bold;">--source</span>
option to supply the single Java source code file, it can effectively
be treated as if it was a scripting language.&nbsp; The Java source
file given to the <span style="font-weight: bold;">--source</span>
option must contain a class with a "main" method and not be included in
a Java package.&nbsp; The source file name (minus the ".java"
extension) must also be identical to the classname.<br>
</div>
</div>
<blockquote>All three methods allow additional
command-line arguments (<span style="font-style: italic;">args</span>)
to be given following <span style="font-weight: bold;">--</span> which
will be passed unaltered to the Java program as the arguments to the
main(String[] args) method of the entry point class. <span
 class="postbody"></span><span class="postbody"><br>
  </span><span style="font-family: monospace;"></span>
  <div style="margin-left: 40px;"><span style="font-family: monospace;">
  </span></div>
</blockquote>
<h3><a name="Information_Options"></a>Information
Options</h3>
<blockquote>The following options provide online information about <span
 style="font-weight: bold;">pljava</span>(1)
and then immediately
exit:</blockquote>
<blockquote><b><a name="--help"></a>--help</b><br>
  <blockquote>Prints a brief usage message and exits.<br>
  </blockquote>
  <b><a name="--html-help"></a>--html-help</b><br>
  <blockquote>Opens this page using the default web browser.<br>
  </blockquote>
  <b><a name="--version_"></a>--version</b><br>
  <blockquote>Prints the version number of this software and exits.<br>
  </blockquote>
  <b><a name="--release-date"></a>--release-date</b><br>
  <blockquote> Prints date that this software was released and exits.<br>
  </blockquote>
  <b><a name="--copyright"></a>--copyright</b><br>
  <blockquote> Prints the <a href="#Copyright"><span
 style="font-weight: bold;">copyright notice</span></a> for this
software and exits.<br>
  </blockquote>
  <span style="font-weight: bold;"><a name="--license"></a>--license<br>
  <br>
  </span>
  <div style="margin-left: 40px;"><span style="font-weight: bold;"></span><span
 style="font-weight: bold;"></span>Prints the <a
 href="#License_Agreement"><span style="font-weight: bold;">license
agreement</span></a> for this software and exits.</div>
</blockquote>
